&lt;h1&gt;Note:&lt;/h1&gt;
A CloudVM is a bunch of resources which can be used to create virtual machines. Each CloudVM can hold several different VMs not only one instances. This machines can communicate in a private network together. You can split your ordered resources between all of this virtual machines. You can create new instances as long as you have enough free resources for the instance. A CloudVM is a virtual data center which can host different instances in one service and you can change the resources you have between all of them.

